nbsEfmMib.name: nbsEfmMib
nbsEfmMib.contactinfo: For technical support, please contact your service channel
nbsEfmMib.description: Private MRV MIB for representing 802.3ah (Ethernet in the First Mile) information

nbsEfmObjects.name: nbsEfmObjects
nbsEfmObjects.description: all MIB objects in nbsEfm MIB.

nbsEfmOamEntry.name: nbsEfmOamEntry
nbsEfmOamEntry.description: Contains a desription of a particular Oam. There are two entries for each OAM link, one entry for the local side, one for the remote.

nbsEfmPhysicalIfIndex.name: nbsEfmPhysicalIfIndex
nbsEfmPhysicalIfIndex.description: ifIndex from the MIB-II Interface Table for the physical port on which this OAM traffic flows.

nbsEfmOamIfIndex.name: nbsEfmOamIfIndex
nbsEfmOamIfIndex.description: ifIndex from the MIB-II Interface Table for this OAM interface.

nbsEfmOamPeerIfIndex.name: nbsEfmOamPeerIfIndex
nbsEfmOamPeerIfIndex.description: ifIndex from the MIB-II Interface Table for the physical port on the other side of the OAM link. For example, if this table entry corresponds to a local OAM device, this object would hold the ifIndex of the remote port.

nbsEfmOamMode.name: nbsEfmOamMode
nbsEfmOamMode.description: A GET operation returns the current mode of the OAM sublayer entity (see 57.2.6), either passive or active. A SET operation changes the mode of operation of the OAM entity to the indicated value. A SET operation shall have no effect on a device whose mode cannot be changed through management or that can only operate in a single mode.

nbsEfmOamCfg.name: nbsEfmOamCfg
nbsEfmOamCfg.description: A string of three bits corresponding to the OAM Configuration field (see Table 57-7) in the most recently received Information OAMPDU. The first bit corresponds to the OAM Mode bit in the OAM Configuration field. The second bit corresponds to the Unidirectional Support bit in the OAM Configuration field. The third bit corresponds to the Loopback Support bit in the OAM Configuration field. This value is updated on reception of a valid frame, with (1) destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in Table 43B-3, (4) the OAM code equals the OAM Information code.

nbsEfmOamPduCfg.name: nbsEfmOamPduCfg
nbsEfmOamPduCfg.description: An eleven bit value corresponding to the Maximum PDU Size value within the OAMPDU Configuration field (see Table 57-8) in the most recently sent Information OAMPDU. This value is updated on reception of a valid frame, with (1) destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in Table 43B-3, (4) the OAM code equals the OAM Information code.

nbsEfmOamFlagsField.name: nbsEfmOamFlagsField
nbsEfmOamFlagsField.description: A string of five bits corresponding to the Flags field (see Table 57-3) in the most recently transmitted OAMPDU. The first bit corresponds to the Link Fault bit in the Flags field. The second bit corresponds to the Dying Gasp bit in the Flags field. The third bit corresponds to the Critical Event bit in the Flags field. The fourth bit corresponds to the Remote Stable bit in the Flags field. The fifth bit corresponds to the Local Stable bit in the Flags field.

nbsEfmOamState.name: nbsEfmOamState
nbsEfmOamState.description: A string of three bits corresponding to the State field (see Table 57-6) of the most recently sent Information OAMPDU. The first and second bits corresponds to the Parser Action bits in the State field. The third bit corresponds to the Multiplexer Action bit in the State field. This value is updated on reception of a valid frame, with (1) destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in Table 43B-3, (4) a OAMPDU code equal to the Information code as specified in Table 57-4.

nbsEfmOamVendorOUI.name: nbsEfmOamVendorOUI
nbsEfmOamVendorOUI.description: The value of the OUI variable in the Vendor Identifier field (see Table 57-9) of the most recently sent Information OAMPDU. This value is updated on reception of a valid frame, with (1) destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in Table 43B-3, (4) a OAMPDU code equal to the Information code as specified in Table 57-4.

nbsEfmOamVendorDeviceId.name: nbsEfmOamVendorDeviceId

This value is updated on reception of a valid frame, with (1) destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in Table 43B-3, (4) a OAMPDU code equal to the Information code as specified in Table 57-4.

nbsEfmOamVendorDeviceVersion.name: nbsEfmOamVendorDeviceVersion

nbsEfmOamPDUTx.name: nbsEfmOamPDUTx
nbsEfmOamPDUTx.description: A count of OAMPDUs passed to the OAM subordinate sublayer for transmission. This counter is incremented when a OAM:MA_DATA.request service service primitive is generated within the OAM sublayer.

nbsEfmOamPDURx.name: nbsEfmOamPDURx
nbsEfmOamPDURx.description: A count of OAMPDUs passed by the OAM subordinate sublayer to the OAM sublayer. This counter is incremented on reception of a valid frame with (1) a destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in Table 43B-3.

nbsEfmOamUnsupportedCodesRx.name: nbsEfmOamUnsupportedCodesRx
nbsEfmOamUnsupportedCodesRx.description: A count of OAMPDUs received that contain an OAM code from Table 57-4 that are not supported by the device. This counter is incremented on reception of a valid frame with (1) destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in Table 43B-3, (4) an OAM code for a function that is not supported by the device.

nbsEfmOamInformationTx.name: nbsEfmOamInformationTx
nbsEfmOamInformationTx.description: A count of OAMPDUs passed to the OAM subordinate sublayer for transmission that contain the OAM Information code specified in Table CROSS REF 57-4. This counter is incremented when a OAM:MA_DATA.request service primitive is generated within the OAM sublayer with an OAM code indicating an OAM Information operation.

nbsEfmOamInformationRx.name: nbsEfmOamInformationRx

nbsEfmOamEventNotificationTx.name: nbsEfmOamEventNotificationTx

nbsEfmOamUniEventNotificationRx.name: nbsEfmOamUniEventNotificationRx
nbsEfmOamUniEventNotificationRx.description: A count of the OAMPDUs received that contain the Event Notification code specified in Table 57-4. This counter is incremented on reception of a valid frame, with (1) destinationField equal to the reserved multicast address for Slow_Protocols specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-1, (2) lengthOrType field value equal to the reserved Type for Slow_Protocols as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-2, (3) a Slow_Protocols subtype value equal to the subtype reserved for OAM as specified in CROSS REF Table 43B-3, (4) the OAM code equals the Event Notification code, (5) the Sequence Number field is not equal to the Sequence Number field of the last received Event Notification OAMPDU and is supported by the device.

nbsEfmOamDupEventNotificationRx.name: nbsEfmOamDupEventNotificationRx

nbsEfmOamErrSymPerCfgDuration.name: nbsEfmOamErrSymPerCfgDuration
nbsEfmOamErrSymPerCfgDuration.description: An eight-octet value indicating the duration of the Errored Symbol Period Event (see 57.5.3.1) window, in terms of symbols.

This integer is updated when a OAM:MA_DATA.request service primitive is generated within the OAM sublayer with an OAMPDU Code field value equal to the Event Notification code as specified in Table 57-4 and Event TLV Type field equal to the Errored Symbol Period Event value as specified in Table 57-10.

nbsEfmOamFramesLostDueToOamError.name: nbsEfmOamFramesLostDueToOamError
nbsEfmOamFramesLostDueToOamError.description: A count of frames that would otherwise be transmitted by the OAM sublayer, but could not be due to an internal OAM sublayer transmit error. If this counter is incremented, then none of the other counters in this section are incremented. The exact meaning and mechanism for incrementing this counter is implementation dependent.

nbsEfmOamAdminState.name: nbsEfmOamAdminState
nbsEfmOamAdminState.description: A value that identifies the operational state of the OAM sublayer. An interface which can provide the OAM sublayer functions specified in Clause 57 will be enabled to do so when this attribute has the enumeration enable(3). When this attribute has the enumeration disable(2) the interface will act as it would if it had no OAM sublayer.

nbsEfmOamOperState.name: nbsEfmOamOperState
nbsEfmOamOperState.description: This object declares configurable (*) and operational reasons for disabling OAM service. The reason applies only if the bit is set. Multiple bits may be set concurrently. OAM service is enabled when no bits are set. Bit Reason to disable --- ---------------------------------------------- 0 reserved 1 reserved 2 reserved 3 reserved 4 reserved 5 Temporarily disabled for download processing 6 Administratively disabled (*) 7 OAM service is not available OCTET STRING bitmasks count the leftmost bit (MSB) as 0.
